FBIS3-12328 "drnes039dd_94001" FBIS-NES-94-039 Document Type:Daily Report 28 Feb 1994 Palestinian Affairs 'Arafat Reacts to Massacre at Hebron Mosque Insists on UN Resolution NC2702065394 London MBC Television in Arabic 2100 GMT 26 Feb 94 NC2702065394 London MBC Television Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Interview with PLO Chairman Yasir 'Arafat by MBC Tunis correspondent Mufidah Hashani in Tunis on 26 February; recorded] [Text] ['Arafat] The most important [word indistinct] is international protection for (?our people). We must see a solution for these settlements and the armed settlers, because they have proven to be time bombs liable to explode at any moment whether we pursue the negotiations or [words indistinct]. The situation may explode at any moment. They are time bombs. [Hashani] What do you expect from the Security Council's meeting tonight? ['Arafat] We are in continuous contact with the U.S. Administration on this issue because we insist on a resolution from the Security Council, not just a condemnation of [words indistinct]. [Hashani] Where have the negotiations between you and the United States reached? ['Arafat] They are continuing. [Hashani] Any idea about the resolution expected to be passed? ['Arafat, interrupting] [Words indistinct] but as I said, we are continuing our contacts with the U.S. Administration on this issue. [Hashani] What about tomorrow's meeting with the Palestinian negotiators who were recalled by the PLO for a meeting in Tunis? Other than the settlements issue, can you clarify other topics of the meeting's agenda? ['Arafat] I prefer not to talk too much and would rather like the deeds do the talking. There will be a complete and comprehensive assessment and afterward we will make a decision.
